  "original_title": "Sri Lanka schedules 3-hour power cuts for Aug 22",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka schedules 3-hour power cuts for Aug 22",
      "author": "Dulya de Silva",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka will experience 3 hours of power cuts on Monday August 22, Public Utilities Commission (PUCSL) Chairman Janaka Ratnayake said.",
        "All areas (A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H, I, J, K, L, P, Q, R, S, T, U, V and W) will have power cuts of 1 hours and 40 minutes between 10.30 am and 06.00 pm and 1 hour 20 minutes from 06.00pm to 10.00 pm.",
        "The daily scheduled power cuts which were reduced to one hour due to the availability of hydropower were extended due to a sudden breakdown in a generator in the Norochcholai coal power plant.",
        "Repairs are underway, and officials said the system was scheduled to be back online by Monday 29.",
        "West Coast and other fuel power Plants are being used to manage supply, officials said, while Unit 2 of Norochcholai is undergoing scheduled maintenance activities.\u00a0 (Colombo/Aug02/2022)"
      ],
